2 1-inch slices banana
1 tablespoon vanilla ice cream
1 teaspoon chocolate sauce
1 teaspoon whipped cream
1/4-inch piece of cherry

Steps:

2. Add 6 tiny scoops of ice cream.

3. Top with chocolate sauce, whipped cream and cherry.

node.text:
Ingredients:

2 (1/2-inch) slices rye bread
1/4 teaspoon Russian dressing
Cheese
1/4 teaspoon sauerkraut
2 (1/2-inch) slices corned beef
Butter
1 tiny potato
Oil, for frying
1 tiny pickle

Steps:

1. Spread Russian dressing on bread and top with cheese, sauerkraut and corned beef.

2. Heat butter in pan and grill sandwich until golden brown on both sides.

3. To make chips:  Slice the potato very thinly. Heat oil in small pot.

4. Add chips and fry until golden brown. Serve sandwich with chips and a pickle.

_____________________________________________

node.text:
Ingredients:

Broth:
1 1/2 tablespoons chicken broth
1/4 inch piece ginger
1/4 teaspoon soy sauce
Wontons:
1 teaspoon ground pork
1/8 teaspoon soy sauce
1/4 teaspoon chives
1/8 teaspoon rice vinegar
1/4 teaspoon cornstarch
1/4 teaspoon grated ginger
Pinch crushed red pepper flakes
3 tiny wonton wrappers
Green onions, to garnish

Steps:

1. In a pot, heat all broth ingredients.

2. In a bowl, combine ground pork, soy sauce, chives, rice vinegar, cornstarch, grated ginger and red pepper flakes. Place a tiny pinch of pork mixture in the center of each wonton. Paint one corner with water and fold another corner on top of it. Place in broth and simmer for 4 minutes. Garnish with chives.

____________________________________

Ingredients:

1/2 teaspoon mayonnaise
1/2 teaspoon ketchup
1/8 teaspoon chopped dill pickles
1/8 teaspoon mustard
Salt and pepper
Pinch sugar
Dash apple cider vinegar
1/2 teaspoon sliced onion
1/8 teaspoon oil
Oil for frying
1 tiny potato, cut into thin fries
1 tiny piece American cheese, melted

Steps:

1. In a small bowl, combine mayo, ketchup, pickles, mustard, salt, pepper, sugar and vinegar.

2. Sauté onion in 1/8 teaspoon oil until caramelized.

3. Heat oil in a pot and cook fries. Place cheese on top of fries as soon as they are done. Top with caramelized onions and sauce.

1 tablespoon water, divided
1/2 teaspoon sugar
1/2 teaspoon butterfly pea flowers
1 teaspoon fresh squeezed lemon juice

Steps:

1. In a saucepan, add half the water and butterfly pea flowers and bring to a simmer.

2. Allow to steep for 10 minutes.

3. Combine remaining water and lemon juice. Strain the pea flower water and stir in sugar, add to a pitcher, pour lemon water over the top.

4. Watch the color begin to change and then stir to combine.

Ingredients:

1 tablespoon milk
1/2 teaspoon cornstarch
1/4 teaspoon sugar
1 vanilla bean, split and scraped
1 wedge of lemon
1-inch piece of pie dough
1/4 teaspoon raspberry jam
1 raspberry, blackberry and strawberry
Mint leaf and whipped cream, for garnish

Steps:

1. Add milk to a saucepan with sugar and cornstarch. Whisk to combine.

2. Add vanilla bean and squeeze in lemon juice and add lemon zest. Transfer mixture to a dish and place in refrigerator to cool.

3. Roll out pie dough and press into pie pan. Fill with dried beans. Bake at 375 degrees for 8 minutes. Remove beans.

4. Spread a layer of jam on the pie crust and top with pudding. Top with fresh berries, whipped cream and a mint leaf.

#TinyTuesday Spotlight✨ Meet Akın Tek @miniceramicsart 

Akın Tek is a self-taught mini ceramics artist, working on a mini throwing wheel he designed and made himself. After 20 years of experience as an academic on critical reading and writing, he quit academia and turned his lifelong hobby to @miniceramicsart.

Tek believes that we grown-ups always cast a dull gaze on everything we get to see. We take them for granted, all is set and standardized for us. However, when scales shift, we find that our minds shift, too. This brings back our sense of astonishment and we see things anew. We care for and connect them as we did in our childhood, where almost everything has a tint of miracle.

“Ceramic artist @defnesamman was the first to encourage me to try my hand at mini ceramics. When I took my first tiny piece off the wheel, I remember that stupid smile on my face, made up of a sense of awe.  Since then, every single mini piece has given me and my followers that smile."

——————————————
Be sure to check out @miniceramicsart for more amazing creations and keep an eye out on our future recipes to see if you can spot any of Akın’s work that was so generously sent to us! ❤️

This Tiny Unicorn Cake Is So Magical 🥺🦄✨

Ingredients:

1 1/2 tablespoons flour
1/4 teaspoon baking powder
1/4 teaspoon baking soda
1/2 teaspoon sugar
1 teaspoon milk
1 teaspoon vegetable oil
1 quail egg, beaten
1 tablespoon vanilla icing
1 tablespoon fondant
Pink luster dust
Edible marker
Candy stars

Steps:

1. Mix dry ingredients for cake, then add milk, vegetable oil and egg.

2. Pour into cake pan and bake at 350 degrees for 5 minutes. Allow to cool and cover with icing.

3. Roll out fondant and cover cake. Form a tiny bit of fondant into the shape of a unicorn horn and paint with pink luster dust. Adhere to the top of the cake with icing. Also adhere stars to the top of the cake. Draw eyes with edible marker and paint cheeks with pink luster dust.

Steps:
